Title:
How to Maintain Trade‑Secret Protection Using Your Private Vault

Body:
Trade‑secret protection only exists when your private information is kept confidential, controlled, and intentionally 
protected. Your private vault is the environment that preserves this protection.

The following materials must always remain private: internal logic, system mechanics, prototypes, drafts, development 
notes, backend workflows, JSON vaults, unreleased designs, and any content not intended for public release. Once private
information is made public, it immediately loses trade‑secret status.

The public vault is only for public‑safe materials such as badges, announcements, and creator‑facing assets. It is not 
for internal logic or confidential work. Keeping private data in your private vault ensures confidentiality, continuity, 
lineage, and defensibility.

This system protects creators by keeping private and public layers separate.
Private vault = trade secret.
Public vault = continuity.
